page.title: 09WHINNEY WOOD
page.content: This section is mainly grass fields which are used for{grazing.}There is a small area of{mixed woodland}and two small{ponds.}A line of{electricty {pylons}also crosses through the area.The{boundaries}in most fields are{hedges}and wooden{fences.}Most fields were grass fields which were being used to graze{sheep.}There was also a field full of yellow plants which were called{oil seed rape.}This is used to make{margarine.}There were many kinds of plants and shrubs lining the roadside,for example,{Bramble {bushes, Wild Rose ,Sycamore, Holly, {Elderberry, Ivy and Gorse. It was a fairly quiet area and we saw many different kinds of{insects}as we walked along.In one field we saw several{wild rabbits}and also a {pheasant.
